<item>
            <title>[LU-17189] GDS is not working on master</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17189</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;GDS on Lustre is not working any more; it&apos;s broken by this commit f792297212387c2ff1b1dd6ead1e2d451a375ade around the same time last year.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In particular, this line and similar ones:&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
tx-&amp;gt;tx_gpu = msg_md ? (msg_md-&amp;gt;md_flags &amp;amp; LNET_MD_FLAG_GPU) : 0;&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
is problematic since `tx_gpu` is a single bit. It will take the last bit of `(msg_md-&amp;gt;md_flags &amp;amp; LNET_MD_FLAG_GPU)` in this assignment that will definitely be zero.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s fair to have a dedicated function to do this check. Patch is coming soon&lt;/p&gt;</description>
